				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I know the whole thing would be more like a new class, but I was just thinking of something for us that magicians could do without some other class won't whine about us getting that would make us too powerful.
<br />

<br />
I think we need to be better with our pets than ANY beastlord.  True, a beastlord is a pet class like us, but they get a number of shaman spells, buffs, debuffs and such, all that can be cast on them, their pets, and group members.  They get pet proc spells, better pet heals, fair melee ability, and several other powers which mages do not.  So they're kind of a combination monk/shaman with a better pet and some better spells.
<br />

<br />
As a magician, much (I would say the majority) of our class power lies in our pets.  Without them we are a fairly weak class.  We melee like a caster (which we should), we have good nukes, but no way to do real CC for ourselves, and we have one castable buff: our DS (yes, I know the summoned items with effects, but I'm looking at combat spells atm).
<br />

<br />
It would be nice to heal our pets as effectively as a beastlord, since we are MORE reliant on our pets than they are, than any other class, in fact.  It would be nice to find a way to boost our effectiveness as a class overall with that in mind.
<br />

<br />
I'd like the non-combat snare, and elemental-based pet-proc spells in keeping with our elemental pets.  But I also know that I don't want to have spells common to a lot of other classes.  
<br />

<br />
So I guess, what I'm trying to say is that I know the Elemental Game isn't the way magicians are, but I thought I'd post it to see if it would inspre other ideas/ways for us to become a better and more interesting class that would be in keeping with our elemental nature.<br />_________________<br />Learn as if you will Live forever.
<br />
Live as if you will Die tomorrow.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
